{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/linux/build-grub-from-source","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>I wonder if there is a UI framework for making minimalistic and beautiful apps that work without OS, the things that we see in UEFI settings like this:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 650px; flex:1.7717391304347827;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/be5abf99e31624285b9a736648a29640/0f98f/uefi-min.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.44171779141104%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"UEFI settings on GIGABYTE motherboard\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/be5abf99e31624285b9a736648a29640/6aca1/uefi-min.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/be5abf99e31624285b9a736648a29640/d2f63/uefi-min.jpg 163w,\n/static/be5abf99e31624285b9a736648a29640/c989d/uefi-min.jpg 325w,\n/static/be5abf99e31624285b9a736648a29640/6aca1/uefi-min.jpg 650w,\n/static/be5abf99e31624285b9a736648a29640/7c09c/uefi-min.jpg 975w,\n/static/be5abf99e31624285b9a736648a29640/01ab0/uefi-min.jpg 1300w,\n/static/be5abf99e31624285b9a736648a29640/0f98f/uefi-min.jpg 1920w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"build-grub\" style=\"position:relative;\">Build GRUB<a href=\"#build-grub\" aria-label=\"build grub permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">git</span> clone https://git.savannah.gnu.org/git/grub.git\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">cd</span> grub\n\n./bootstrap\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># EFI</span>\n./configure <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  --with-platform<span class=\"token operator\">=</span>efi <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--target</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>x86_64 <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  --disable-werror <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--prefix</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token builtin class-name\">pwd</span><span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>/<span class=\"token punctuation\">..</span>/grub-install\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># BIOS</span>\n./configure <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  --with-platform<span class=\"token operator\">=</span>pc <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--target</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>i386 <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  --disable-werror <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--prefix</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token builtin class-name\">pwd</span><span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>/<span class=\"token punctuation\">..</span>/grub-install\n\n<span class=\"token function\">make</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">make</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span>\n\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">cd</span> <span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token builtin class-name\">pwd</span><span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>/<span class=\"token punctuation\">..</span>/grub-install/bin\n\n<span class=\"token function\">find</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">..</span>/lib/grub/x86_64-efi <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-name</span> <span class=\"token string\">'*.mod'</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">sed</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-e</span> <span class=\"token string\">'s/..\\/lib\\/grub\\/x86_64-efi\\///g'</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">sed</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-e</span> <span class=\"token string\">'s/\\.mod//g'</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">sort</span> <span class=\"token operator\">></span> modules.list\n\n./grub-mkimage <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--format</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>x86_64-efi <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--output</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>bootx64.efi <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--prefix</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">'(tftp,192.168.3.146)/grub'</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--verbose</span> <span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>modules.list<span class=\"token operator\">|</span><span class=\"token function\">tr</span> <span class=\"token string\">'\\n'</span> <span class=\"token string\">' '</span><span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span> <span class=\"token operator\">></span> grub-mkimage.log <span class=\"token operator\"><span class=\"token file-descriptor important\">2</span>></span><span class=\"token file-descriptor important\">&amp;1</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\"># modules = efinet tftp chain</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Building BIOS version you can get this error:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">/usr/bin/ld: relocatable linking with relocations from format elf64-x86-64 (lib/zstd/zstd_module-debug.o) to format elf32-i386 (zstd.module) is not supported</code></pre></div>\n<p>TODO - how to fix it?</p>\n<p>References:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.drlm.org/en/latest/building_grub2.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">DRLM Docs</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://gitlab.archlinux.org/archlinux/packaging/packages/grub/-/blob/main/PKGBUILD?ref_type=heads\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://gitlab.archlinux.org/archlinux/packaging/packages/grub/-/blob/main/PKGBUILD?ref_type=heads</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"font-customization\" style=\"position:relative;\">Font customization<a href=\"#font-customization\" aria-label=\"font customization permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">./grub-mkfont <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-s</span> <span class=\"token number\">24</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-o</span> Sarabun_24.pf2 Sarabun-Regular.ttf\n./grub-mkfont <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-s</span> <span class=\"token number\">16</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-o</span> Sarabun_16.pf2 Sarabun-Regular.ttf\n./grub-mkfont <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-s</span> <span class=\"token number\">32</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-o</span> Sarabun_32.pf2 Sarabun-Regular.ttf</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"edk2\" style=\"position:relative;\">edk2<a href=\"#edk2\" aria-label=\"edk2 permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>Build edk2 example</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> pacman <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-Syu</span> nasm\n\n<span class=\"token function\">git</span> clone https://github.com/tianocore/edk2.git\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">cd</span> edk2\n<span class=\"token function\">git</span> submodule update <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--init</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">source</span> edksetup.sh BaseTools\n<span class=\"token comment\"># turn off warnings as errors: modify settings under Conf/tools_def.txt</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\"># to remove the warnings-as-errors flag </span>\n<span class=\"token comment\"># ref: https://edk2-devel.narkive.com/i74qD279/edk2-how-to-turnoff-error-c2220-warning-treated-as-error-edk-ii</span>\n\n<span class=\"token function\">make</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-C</span> BaseTools/Source/C</code></pre></div>\n<ul>\n<li>edit Conf/target.txt</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">TARGET_ARCH           = X64\nTOOL_CHAIN_TAG        = GCC</code></pre></div>\n<ul>\n<li>create MyHelloWrold/MyHelloWrold.c</li>\n<li>create MyHelloWrold/MyHelloWrold.inf</li>\n<li>edit ShellPkg/ShellPkg.dsc</li>\n<li>add into [Components]: <code class=\"language-text\">MyHelloWorld/MyHelloWorld.inf</code></li>\n<li>if you see <strong>BaseTools C Tool binary was not found (GenFw)</strong> you may need to run</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">make -C /scgames/installer/edk2/BaseTools/Source/C</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"other-links\" style=\"position:relative;\">Other links<a href=\"#other-links\" aria-label=\"other links permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<h3 id=\"gfxboot\" style=\"position:relative;\">gfxboot<a href=\"#gfxboot\" aria-label=\"gfxboot permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://en.opensuse.org/SDB:Gfxboot\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://en.opensuse.org/SDB:Gfxboot</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wiki.ubuntu.com/CdBootloader\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://wiki.ubuntu.com/CdBootloader</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/openSUSE/gfxboot\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/openSUSE/gfxboot</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/openSUSE/gfxboot/blob/master/doc/suse.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/openSUSE/gfxboot/blob/master/doc/suse.jpg</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"dnsmasq-configuration\" style=\"position:relative;\">dnsmasq configuration<a href=\"#dnsmasq-configuration\" aria-label=\"dnsmasq configuration permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://yulistic.gitlab.io/2018/03/configuring-dnsmasq-only-for-dhcp-server-in-ubuntu-pc/\" title=\"smartCard-inline\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://yulistic.gitlab.io/2018/03/configuring-dnsmasq-only-for-dhcp-server-in-ubuntu-pc/</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/dnsmasq\" title=\"smartCard-inline\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/dnsmasq</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://serverfault.com/questions/829068/trouble-with-dnsmasq-dhcp-proxy-pxe-for-uefi-clients\" title=\"smartCard-inline\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://serverfault.com/questions/829068/trouble-with-dnsmasq-dhcp-proxy-pxe-for-uefi-clients</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/operating-systems/oracle-linux/6/install/ol-dnsmasq-conf.html\" title=\"smartCard-inline\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://docs.oracle.com/en/operating-systems/oracle-linux/6/install/ol-dnsmasq-conf.html</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"uefi-bootloader\" style=\"position:relative;\">UEFI bootloader<a href=\"#uefi-bootloader\" aria-label=\"uefi bootloader permalink\" cl